Avid Technology, Inc. Key Developments

Global News Chooses Avid Graphics and Virtual Reality Solutions to Enrich its Storytelling
Jun 23 17
Avid announced that Global News has selected Avid graphics solutions to transform the look and feel of news delivered across its platforms. Global News selected Avid’s comprehensive tools and workflow solutions for graphics creation for its four main production centers, as well as nine other remote broadcast locations. Powered by the MediaCentral® Platform, the industry’s most open, tightly integrated and efficient platform designed for media, the new workflow includes Avid’s Maestro graphics suite, 4Designer 2D/3D authoring software and ProSet virtual studio. As well as delivering a fast-turnaround workflow, the system functions as a large distributed model and virtualizes nearly all of the news produced by Global News. The new workflow also brings speed and agility to Global News’ production centers. Set elements can be constructed in a day or even a few hours, allowing crews to create a high volume of news stories with vibrant, realistic graphics under very tight timeframes.


KTBS-TV Chooses Avid to Modernize its News and Production Workflow
Jun 9 17
Avid announced that KTBS-TV, has revamped its production and news workflow and expanded its storage capacity with two of the industry’s tools: the Avid MediaCentral Platform, the industry’s most open, tightly integrated and efficient platform designed for media, and Avid NEXIS. By adopting the comprehensive set of tools and workflow solutions for creating, distributing and optimizing media, KTBS will be able to simplify its workflows, enable collaboration between different departments, and quickly distribute content across multiple platforms. After evaluating various options, KTBS decided to invest in end-to-end solutions based on its previous experience with Avid. Using its new Avid workflow, all of KTBS’ data will reside in a central location to facilitate collaboration between its newsroom, production, and promotions departments, giving access and shared content to all users.


Avid Technology, Inc. Reports Consolidated Unaudited Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Reaffirm Earnings Guidance for Full Year 2017
May 10 17
Avid Technology, Inc. reported consolidated unaudited earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total net revenues were $104,107,000 against $143,547,000 reported last year. Operating income was $3,083,000 against $25,758,000 reported last year. Loss before income taxes was $1,763,000 against income of $21,575,000 reported last year. Net loss was $1,915,000 or $0.05 basic and diluted against income of $20,940,000 or $0.53 basic and diluted reported last year. Non-GAAP revenue was $104,107,000 against $143,816,000 reported last year. Non-GAAP operating income was $9,436,000 against $34,938,000 reported last year. Adjusted EBITDA was $13,006,000 against $38,549,000 reported last year. GAAP net cash provided by operating activities was $3,534,000 against GAAP net cash used in operating activities of $11,209,000 reported last year. Capital expenditures were $1,729,000 against $4,518,000 reported last year. Free cash inflow was $1,805,000 against outflow of $15,727,000 reported last year. Adjusted free cash inflow was $6,758,000 against outflow of $9,440,000 reported last year. Purchases of property and equipment were $1,729,000 against $4,518,000 reported last year.
c
The company also re-affirmed its full year 2017 earnings guidance. The company expected revenue in the range of $93 million to $103 million, adjusted EBITDA to be in the range of $6 million to $12 million and adjusted free cash outflow in the range of $4 million - inflow of $4 million.


